					σ-ﬁelds σ(X1), . . . , σ(Xn) are independent. This is equivalent to saying that the &nbsp;
					property &nbsp;
					P({X1 ∈ F1} ∩ . . . ∩ {Xn ∈ Fn}) = P(X1 ∈ F1) . . . P(Xn ∈ Fn) &nbsp;
					(9.1) &nbsp;
